<h2>Local Content Strategy Checklist</h2>
<p>Blog content builds <a href="/glossary/topical-authority/">topical authority</a>, captures informational searches, and creates internal links to your service pages. Businesses that publish 4+ posts per month rank for 3x more keywords.</p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] <strong>Publish at least 4 blog posts per month.</strong> Target keywords your customers search for. Mix informational ("how much does [service] cost") with commercial ("best [service] in [city]").</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Create a content calendar.</strong> Plan 30 to 60 days ahead. Batch creation monthly. See our <a href="/blog/create-content-calendar-seo/">content calendar guide</a>.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Write location-specific content.</strong> "How [City] Weather Affects Your [Product/Service]" and "[City] Guide to [Topic]" rank well and attract local links.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Write cost guides for your services.</strong> "How Much Does [Service] Cost in [City]?" is one of the highest-converting content types for local businesses.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Answer questions your customers actually ask.</strong> Pull from Google's People Also Ask, your own FAQ page, and customer service calls.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Link every blog post to at least 2 service pages.</strong> This builds internal link authority and pushes ranking power to your money pages.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Optimize every post for <a href="/blog/seo-content-writing/">SEO content writing</a> best practices.</strong> Primary keyword in title, first 100 words, and at least 1 H2.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Repurpose blog content for GBP posts and social media.</strong> Every blog post should generate 2 to 3 GBP posts and at least 1 social media post. This maximizes the value of every piece of content you create.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Technical SEO Checklist</h2>
<p>Technical issues suppress your rankings silently. A broken site prevents everything else from working.</p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] <strong>Install an SSL certificate (HTTPS).</strong> Every page must load securely. Unsecured sites display "Not Secure" warnings that destroy trust.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Achieve under-3-second page load time on mobile.</strong> Compress images. Minimize JavaScript. Use a fast hosting provider.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Pass Core Web Vitals.</strong> Check your scores in Google Search Console. Fix LCP (Largest Contentful Paint), CLS (Cumulative Layout Shift), and INP (Interaction to Next Paint) issues.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Ensure full mobile responsiveness.</strong> Test every page on a phone. Tap-to-call buttons, readable text, and no horizontal scrolling.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Submit an XML sitemap to Google Search Console.</strong> Point Google to every important page on your site. See our <a href="/blog/create-xml-sitemap/">XML sitemap guide</a>.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Optimize your <code>robots.txt</code> file.</strong> Make sure Google can crawl your important pages. See our <a href="/blog/optimize-robots-txt/">robots.txt guide</a>.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Fix broken links.</strong> Run a site crawl to find 404 errors. Redirect or fix every one. See our <a href="/blog/fix-broken-links/">broken link guide</a>.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Set up <a href="/blog/google-analytics-4-setup/">Google Analytics 4</a> and Google Search Console.</strong> Both are free and essential for tracking.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Run a full SEO audit.</strong> Use our free <a href="/tools/seo-audit/">SEO audit tool</a> to identify technical issues, or follow our <a href="/blog/how-to-do-seo-audit/">SEO audit guide</a>.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Link Building Checklist</h2>
<p>Backlinks account for 11% of local pack ranking factors. For local businesses, quality and relevance beat quantity every time.</p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] <strong>Join your local Chamber of Commerce.</strong> Most chambers link to member websites.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Sponsor local events, teams, or charities.</strong> Sponsorship pages almost always include a backlink.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Partner with complementary local businesses.</strong> Cross-referral and cross-link opportunities. A dentist and an orthodontist. A roofer and a general contractor.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Get listed on supplier or manufacturer websites.</strong> If you are a certified installer or authorized dealer, ask for a link on their "find a partner" page.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Offer expert commentary to local media.</strong> Local journalists need quotes from professionals. Be available and you earn links from news sites.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Create link-worthy content.</strong> Cost guides, local statistics, and original research earn natural backlinks.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Avoid paid link schemes.</strong> Do not buy links. Do not participate in link exchanges that violate Google's guidelines. A few quality local links beat hundreds of spammy ones.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Earn links from local content.</strong> Publish local statistics, cost guides, or neighborhood comparison content that journalists and bloggers reference naturally.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Check competitor backlinks.</strong> Use Ahrefs or Semrush to see where your top local competitors get their links. Replicate the best ones.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Why Local Links Matter More Than Generic Ones</h3>
<p>A link from your city's Chamber of Commerce page carries more local ranking value than a link from a national blog with 10x the domain authority. Google weighs geographic relevance for local search. Five local links from businesses, news sites, and organizations in your service area outperform 50 generic links from unrelated websites.</p>
<p>For more detail, see our guide on <a href="/blog/build-backlinks-for-blog/">building backlinks for blogs</a>.</p>
<h2>Tracking and Measurement Checklist</h2>
<p>SEO without measurement is guesswork. Set up tracking before you start optimizing so you can see the impact of every change.</p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] <strong>Track local pack rankings.</strong> Monitor your position for 15 to 20 target keywords. Check weekly.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Monitor organic traffic in Google Analytics.</strong> Set up location-based segments to isolate local traffic.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Track phone calls from GBP.</strong> GBP Insights shows how many calls your profile generates. Compare month over month.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Track form submissions by source.</strong> Use UTM parameters or GA4 event tracking to identify which pages and channels drive leads.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Monitor review volume and rating.</strong> Target 2 to 4 new <a href="/glossary/google-reviews/">Google reviews</a> per month with a 4.5+ average.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Check Google Search Console weekly.</strong> Monitor impressions, clicks, and average position for your target keywords. See our <a href="/blog/google-search-console-guide/">Search Console guide</a>.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Audit your checklist quarterly.</strong> Re-run this entire checklist every 90 days. Local SEO is not a one-time project. It is an ongoing system.</li>
</ul>
